eu.focusnet.app.controller

Class DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.focusnet.app.controller.DataManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ApplicationStatusObserver

    public class DataManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements ApplicationStatusObserver
    The DataManager is responsible for granting access to resources. They may be online or in the local SQlite repository. Other classes may not have to interact with data handling objects such as the DatabaseAdapter or the NetworkManager, and only use this present object. It also contains the required logic to build the application content.

      • cache

        private java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.concurrent.FutureTask<FocusObject>> cache
        An in-memory cache of FocusObjects that helps to speed up the instantiation of the application content, by avoiding to retrieve many time the same resources from the network and/or the local database. It consists of FutureTasks of DataManager.DataRetrievalTasks.

        This cache is only used when initializing the application content instance, and is then freed, as resources are not required after that anymore.

        This cache mechanism is also used to avoid multiple concurrent downloads of the same resource, so it is NOT safe to free it when needing memory.

      • get

        public FocusObject get(java.lang.String url,
                       java.lang.Class targetClass)
        Get the data identified by the provided url.

        This method first tries to acquire the resource from the local cache or database and then from the network if not available. It also stores the object in the local database such that it can later be quickly accessed.

        Parameters:
        url - The URL of the resource to retrieve
        targetClass - The retrieved object will be converted to a Java object matching this class
        Returns:
        A FocusObject, or mor specifically one of its inherited classes matching targetclass, or null if the object could not be retrieved, e.g. because of network error or any other exception raised in DataManager.DataRetrievalTask, or if the task was interrupted.

      • getFutureForGet

        private java.util.concurrent.FutureTask<FocusObject> getFutureForGet(java.lang.String url,
                                                                     java.lang.Class targetClass)
        Acquire the FutureTask matching the resource to get. If the task is not created, yet, do create it and launch data retrieval on the data retrieval pool. If it already exists, simply return a pointer to the task's future such that the caller can wait for the resource to become available.

        This way of organizing code allows us to mark this method as synchronized and hence avoid having multiple parallel downloads of the same resource.

        Parameters:
        url - The URL of the resource to retrieve
        targetClass - The retrieved object will be converted to a Java object matching this class.
        Returns:
        The future of the task

      • create

        public DataManager.ResourceOperationStatus create(FocusObject data)
        Create a new FOCUS data object and send it to the its target location on the network.

        The resource is also saved in the local database for later quicker use. If network is not available, it is only stored in this database and will be pushed to the network later during periodic operations performed by CronService.

        Parameters:
        data - The FocusObject representing the data to create
        Returns:
        ResourceOperationsStatus.SUCESS on success, ResourceOperationsStatus.FAILURE on failure, or ResourceOperationsStatus.PENDING on success but without network connectivity.

        The resource is also saved in the local database for later quicker use. If network is not available, it is only stored in this database and will be pushed to the network later during periodic operations performed by CronService.

        Parameters:
        data - The FocusObject representing the data to update.
        Returns:
        ResourceOperationsStatus.SUCESS on success, ResourceOperationsStatus.FAILURE on failure, or ResourceOperationsStatus.PENDING on success but without network connectivity.

      • delete

        public DataManager.ResourceOperationStatus delete(java.lang.String url)
        Delete an existing FOCUS data object, both locally and on its target location on the network.

        If network is not available, the deletion information is only stored in the local database and deletion will be performed on the network later during periodic operations performed by CronService.

        Parameters:
        url - The URL of the resource to delete.
        Returns:
        ResourceOperationsStatus.SUCESS on success, ResourceOperationsStatus.FAILURE on failure, or ResourceOperationsStatus.PENDING on success but without network connectivity.

      • pushPendingLocalModifications

        public void pushPendingLocalModifications()
                                   throws FocusMissingResourceException
        Push local modifications to the network
        Throws:
        FocusMissingResourceException - If at least one error has been encountered. note that this method is resilient: if an error occurs, it will continue to process the queue of objects to push. This way, if the problem is temporary due to network conditions, it will not have to redo everything on next run. The caller should however take this exception in consideration for its logic, e.g. do not overwrite objects that are have not yet been transmitted to the final network endpoint.
